content.html: Last week, when walking by the lake, I saw the heron that often frequents the area. Of course, I hadn’t taken any cameras with decent zooms with me, so today I popped the little Panasonic in my pocket. It’s not the best bit of kit, but it fits in a pocket. No heron, but instead I was rewarded with a great white egret.

content.html:
This morning I was very lucky to see the only (known) albatross in the northern hemisphere. Quite the handsome bird is Albert!

 

 

Also saw the usual crop of puffins, gannets and razorbills.
